'''Caetano Penna Franco Altafin Rodrigues da Cunha''' (born January 13, 1983) is an entrepreneur, attorney and ocean rower. In 2015, he became the first Brazilian citizen to row across the North Atlantic Ocean after 43 days to promote [[osteosarcoma]] research.<ref name="globoesporte">{{cite web | url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/remo/noticia/2015/01/advogado-larga-emprego-e-vai-cruzar-atlantico-para-financiar-cura-de-cancer.html | title=Advogado larga emprego e vai cruzar Atlântico para financiar cura de câncer | publisher=globo.com | accessdate=14 September 2017 | language=Portuguese | trans-title=Long employed lawyer will cross Atlantic to fund cancer cure}}</ref><ref name="globoesporte2">{{cite web | url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/remo/noticia/2015/04/por-causa-nobre-carioca-encara-fome-sede-e-tubarao-cruzando-o-atlantico.html | title=Por causa nobre, carioca encara fome, sede e tubarão cruzando o Atlântico | publisher=globo.com | accessdate=14 September 2017 | language=Portuguese | trans-title=Carioca faces hunger, thirst and sharks crossing the Atlantic for a noble cause}}</ref><ref name="extraglobo">{{cite web | title=Em busca de um sonho: carioca irá cruzar a remo o Oceano Atlântico para conseguir fundos para pesquisa sobre tumor ósseo | publisher=globo.com | accessdate=14 September 2017 | language=Portuguese | trans-title=In search of a dream: Carioca will row across the Atlantic Ocean to obtain funds for research on bone tumor | url=https://extra.globo.com/noticias/brasil/em-busca-de-um-sonho-carioca-ira-cruzar-remo-oceano-atlantico-para-conseguir-fundos-para-pesquisa-sobre-tumor-osseo-13438086.html}}</ref>

Before, he had founded the NGO Library Tree in 2006, responsible for promoting and creating local libraries in Brazil. He had also founded a Brazilian retail store named MinD in 2014, a home design company. He has a Master of Law from [[Harvard Law School]].<ref name="globoesporte3" />

He was featured in the 2011 documentary ''Bildungsroman''.

