{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = Jornal de Negócios | school = | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | motto = | type = Business newspaper | format = [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|Tabloid]] | owner = [[Cofina]] | founder = <!-- or |founders= --> | publisher = Mediafin-Sociedade Editora | president = | editor = | chiefeditor = | depeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | generalmanager = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | metroeditor = | metrochief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{start date and age|1998}} | political = | language = [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] | ceased publication = | relaunched = | headquarters = [[Lisbon]] | circulation = 10, 501 (2010) | circulation_date = | sister newspapers = ''[[Correio da Manhã]]'' | ISSN = | oclc = | website = {{url|https://www.jornaldenegocios.pt/}} }} '''''Jornal de Negócios''''' (meaning ''Business Newspaper'' in English) is a Portuguese language business newspaper published in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]].
==History and profile== ''Jornal de Negócios'' was started in 1997 as a finance website, being the first in the country.<ref name=voxe>{{cite web|title=Jornal de Negócios|url=http://www.voxeurop.eu/en/content/source-information/364281-jornal-de-negocios|work=VoxEurop|accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref> In 1998 it became a business newspaper<ref name=voxe/> and on 8 May 2003 it began to be published daily.<ref>{{cite web|title=Overview of the Sector|url=http://www.gmcs.pt/en/overview-of-the-sector-20140314-164712|work=GMCS|accessdate=17 May 2015|date=19 May 2014}}</ref>
''Jornal de Negócios'' is owned by [[Cofina]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Business Evolution for the Year 2006|url=http://www.cofina.pt/~/media/Files/C/Cofina/investors/investors/2006archive/businessev06/businessev06-en.pdf|work=Cofina|accessdate=6 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://ejc.net/media_landscapes/portugal|title= Media Landscapes Portugal|author1=Fernando Correia|author2=Carla Martins|accessdate=9 November 2014|work= European Journalism Centre}}</ref> and is based in Lisbon.<ref name=voxe/> Its sister newspaper is ''[[Correio da Manhã]]'', also owned by Cofina.<ref>{{cite book|author=Gustavo Cardoso|title=The Media in the Network Society: Browsing, News, Filters and Citizenship|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PRH7Ay7NOKQC&pg=PA272|accessdate=30 November 2014|date=January 2007|publisher=Lulu.com|isbn=978-1-84753-792-8|page=272}}</ref>{{Self-published inline|date=December 2017}} Both papers are published in tabloid format.<ref name=wan/> The publisher of ''Jornal de Negócios'' is Mediafin-Sociedade Editora.<ref name=wan/>
==Circulation== In 2003 ''Jornal de Negócios'' had a circulation of 10,000 copies.<ref name=wan>{{cite web|title=World Press Trends|url=http://www.wan-press.org/ecrire/upload/wpt2004.pdf|work=World Association of Newspapers|accessdate=8 February 2015|location=Paris|date=2004}}</ref> Its 2004 circulation was 8,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Media pluralism in the Member States of the European Union|url=http://ec.europa.eu/information_society/media_taskforce/doc/pluralism/media_pluralism_swp_en.pdf|work=Commission of the European Communities|accessdate=27 March 2015|location=Brussels|date=16 January 2007}}</ref> In 2007 the paper had a circulation of 8,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|author=Anne Austin et. al. |title=Western Europe Market and Media Fact |url=http://conan.lib.muohio.edu/ebooks/Western_Europe_Market_MediaFact_2008/Western%20Europe%20Market%20&%20MediaFact%202008.pdf |work=Zenith Optimedia |accessdate=11 April 2015 |date=2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205131709/http://conan.lib.muohio.edu/ebooks/Western_Europe_Market_MediaFact_2008/Western%20Europe%20Market%20%26%20MediaFact%202008.pdf |archivedate= 5 February 2015 |df= }}</ref> The circulation of the paper was 10,668 copies in 2009 and 10,501 copies in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=National Newspapers|url=http://www.ifabc.org/site/assets/media/National-Newspapers_total-circulation_IFABC_17-01-13.xls|work=International Federation of Audit Bureaux of Circulations|accessdate=6 March 2015}}</ref>
